    <detaileddescription>
<para>Implements a program to tie the system together.</para><para><linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
It ties together the ROM, RAM and CPU chips and implements multiple runtime targets.</para><para><linebreak/>
<linebreak/>
If SDL is enabled the default runtime will open a window and map the screen region of memory to a SDL window. Otherwise if SDL is disabled, the default and only runtime is the command line debugger. <linebreak/>
 </para><sect1 id="a01570_1Hc07Debugger">
<title>Debugger</title>
